SIMPLE: amortize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amortize
<hw>A*mor"tize</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>amortisen</ets>, LL. <ets>amortisare</ets>, <ets>admortizare</ets>,
F. <ets>amortir</ets> to sell in mortmain, to extinguish; L.
<ets>ad</ets> + <ets>mors</ets> death. See <er>Mortmain</er>]</ety>.
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To make as if dead; to destroy.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>To alienate in mortmain, that is,
to convey to a corporation. See <er>Mortmain</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To clear off or extinguish, as a debt, usually by
means of a sinking fund.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amortizement</ent>⟦br⟧
